# No Barrel Exports

Do not create barrel files that re-export from other modules — including type-only re-exports.

Avoid:

```ts
export * from "./process-runner.js";
export { ShellEnvironment } from "./shell-environment.js";
export type { Thread, Run } from "./thread.js";
```

Prefer direct imports from the defining module or explicit package subpath exports:

```ts
import { ProcessRunner } from "@winnie/backend/cursor-agent/process-runner";
import type { Thread } from "@winnie/contracts/thread";
```

Packages should expose concrete subpaths (via `exports` patterns like `"./*"` for internal packages, or an explicit allowlist for public libs) rather than a root `.` barrel.
